[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    103[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mLocation:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Why-These-Services "Amazon MSK or Amazon MQ for HL7 integration" paragraph ("Most hospital EHR integrations speak HL7 v2 over MLLP (Minimal Lower Layer Protocol), and getting those messages into AWS typically uses an on-premises MLLP receiver that republishes to Amazon MQ (ActiveMQ flavor) or an MSK (Managed Kafka) topic"); Architecture Diagram ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mN[On-Prem MLLP Bridge\n+ Amazon MQ][38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m); Prerequisites EHR Integration row.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    104[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m MLLP itself has no native authentication or encryption (it's TCP framing over a stream socket). Production HL7 v2 deployments wrap MLLP in TLS (often called "MLLP over TLS" or "MLLPS") and authenticate connections via mutual TLS with hospital-issued certificates. The on-premises MLLP bridge is the PHI ingress surface from the hospital's EHR into AWS; it traverses the boundary between the hospital network and the AWS VPC via Site-to-Site VPN or AWS Direct Connect, both of which have their own configuration disciplines. The recipe describes the MLLP bridge as "an on-premises MLLP receiver that republishes to Amazon MQ" without addressing:[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    105[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    106[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m1[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m MLLP-over-TLS vs unencrypted MLLP (the latter is still common in hospital integration engine deployments and is increasingly out of policy).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    107[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m2[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m Site-to-Site VPN vs Direct Connect for the on-premises-to-AWS connection (Direct Connect is the production standard for high-volume PHI ingress; VPN is acceptable for lower volumes).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    108[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m3[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m Mutual TLS or token-based authentication on the MQ broker (the broker is the trust boundary; an unauthenticated broker is a PHI broadcast channel).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    109[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m4[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m Network segmentation: the on-premises bridge should sit in a DMZ or integration tier, not on the hospital's internal clinical network.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    110[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    111[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mThese are standard healthcare-integration disciplines that the recipe assumes the reader has but doesn't name. For a teaching example targeting a mixed audience (executives, architects, engineers, PMs), the omission is more significant than it would be for a pure-engineer audience.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    112[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Add a one-paragraph note to the Why-These-Services Amazon MSK / Amazon MQ paragraph: "The on-premises MLLP receiver is the PHI ingress surface into AWS. Wrap MLLP in TLS (MLLPS) with mutual TLS authentication; deploy the receiver in a DMZ or integration tier, not on the clinical network; connect to AWS via Direct Connect for production volumes (Site-to-Site VPN is acceptable for lower volumes and pilot deployments); authenticate the AWS-side MQ or Kafka broker via mutual TLS or short-lived IAM-derived tokens rather than long-lived shared secrets." Add to Prerequisites EHR Integration row: "MLLP-over-TLS with mutual TLS authentication is the production posture; raw MLLP is acceptable only for development environments with synthetic data."[K
