[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    118[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mLocation:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Why-These-Services "Amazon Bedrock for LLM-assisted triage (optional, advanced)" paragraph; Variations "LLM-assisted clinical-reasoning triage" extension.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    119[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The Bedrock paragraph correctly identifies the experimental nature of LLM-assisted clinical-reasoning triage and the validation requirement ("Expensive and requires rigorous validation. Layer on top of the statistical detection, not a replacement for it"). The Variations extension correctly says the LLM output "is not a replacement for human clinical judgment, and the LLM output has to be validated against clinical experience before being deployed."[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    120[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    121[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mWhat's missing is the BAA-discipline forward reference that Chapter 2's recipes (especially 2.7-2.10) settled as the right framing for generative AI in PHI-bearing flows: BAA coverage of the model and the inference infrastructure, minimum-necessary prompt construction (the prompt should not carry the entire clinical note; it should carry only the data needed for the triage decision), output filtering for clinical-recommendation hallucinations, and a full prompt-and-response audit trail tied to the triage decision. Bedrock with Amazon's foundation models is HIPAA-eligible under the BAA, but third-party models on Bedrock have differing BAA postures, and the recipe's "HIPAA-eligible LLM" framing doesn't differentiate. For a clinical-decision-support use case, this is a non-trivial compliance gap.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    122[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Expand the Bedrock paragraph: "A HIPAA-eligible LLM through Bedrock can compare the dispense event against the patient's recent clinical notes and flag reasoning mismatches. Use only models with BAA coverage on the inference path (Amazon's foundation models on Bedrock are HIPAA-eligible; third-party models on Bedrock have differing BAA postures, and the model's terms of service must be reviewed before PHI-bearing prompts are sent). Construct prompts with minimum-necessary context (the relevant note excerpts, the dispense event, the active medication list; not the full chart), filter outputs for clinical-recommendation hallucinations, and log every prompt and response to the audit trail tied to the triage decision. See Chapter 2's generative AI recipes for the established BAA discipline." Add a forward reference to the Chapter 2 recipes that established this pattern (2.4-2.10).[K
