[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    388[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mLocation:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Opening vignette ("vancomycin 2 grams IV every 8 hours for a 52 kg patient in the step-down unit. The pharmacist's brain does the weight-based math in the background (roughly 38 mg/kg per dose, well above the usual 15-20 mg/kg, and the frequency is aggressive for this patient's renal function based on the creatinine she glanced at earlier)").[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    389[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The math is correct (2000 mg / 52 kg = 38.5 mg/kg per dose; standard vancomycin dosing per IDSA is 15-20 mg/kg per dose q8-12h). The vignette is internally consistent. A minor pharmacokinetic refinement: modern IDSA vancomycin dosing guidance (2020 update) emphasizes AUC-guided dosing rather than trough-only, and the "15-20 mg/kg per dose" figure refers to the loading-dose / maintenance-dose range; some patients legitimately receive higher per-dose vancomycin (25-30 mg/kg) for severe MRSA infections. The vignette's "well above the usual 15-20 mg/kg" is correct as a flag-worthy threshold but doesn't acknowledge the higher-end legitimate dosing range.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    390[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    391[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mThis is LOW because (a) the vignette is illustrative and the flag is correctly identified as worth pharmacist attention even at 25-30 mg/kg per dose because the frequency (q8h) compounds the issue, (b) the vignette's narrative thread (the pharmacist's mental math saved an AKI) is the correct teaching example regardless of the specific threshold, and (c) the recipe's prose elsewhere correctly addresses indication-aware and pharmacokinetic-aware dosing. The fix is a one-clause caveat.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    392[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Either (a) leave the vignette as-is (it's narratively strong and the threshold is approximately correct) or (b) add a one-clause caveat: "(roughly 38 mg/kg per dose, well above the usual 15-20 mg/kg per dose for routine use, and even above the higher 25-30 mg/kg per dose used for severe MRSA infections, and the frequency is aggressive for this patient's renal function ...)". Option (a) is the smaller editorial change; option (b) preempts a clinically-savvy reader's pushback and is consistent with the recipe's elsewhere-careful pharmacokinetic framing. The Honest Take and Where it Struggles are already clinically careful, so option (b) maintains tonal consistency.[K
