[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    418[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mPattern: A6 (amoxicillin pediatric dose threshold) and the indication-aware dosing prose are connected.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The prose correctly identifies indication-aware dosing as a discipline ("The drug's standard mg/kg/day dose by indication (otitis media vs. pneumonia vs. UTI)"), but the sample alert hard-codes a threshold that's inconsistent with current AAP high-dose-AOM guidance for the indication the sample uses. The asymmetry is the same kind of teaching-fidelity gap as A3: the prose makes a discipline claim and the example doesn't reflect it.[K
