[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    162[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m1[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe audit trail does not specify which policy was active at the time of an inference.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m A household-membership record written under [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140msuppress_entire_group_if_any_suppressed[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m has different semantics than one written under [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mexclude_suppressed_from_group[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m; the policy in effect is not stored on the record. A subsequent forensic review (a domestic-violence-survivor patient learns the household graph leaked her location and asks the institution to investigate) cannot reconstruct the policy state at the time of the inference.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    163[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    164[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m2[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mPolicy changes are not architectural events.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe's "the policy decision has to be made by the privacy office" framing implies the policy is decision-level; the architecture should treat the policy-change as an event that triggers re-inference of all affected records (otherwise records inferred under the old policy persist with the old semantics indefinitely).[K
